cienaCesAclMIB.name: cienaCesAclMIB

revisions.description: Created new Extended table for the ACL rules which is indexed by both source and destination IP. Deprecated the cienaCesAclTable. Added new global counter for bad protocol.

cienaCesAclMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
cienaCesAclMIB.description: This module defines the ACL details and the associated notifications.

cienaCesAclAdminState.name: cienaCesAclAdminState
cienaCesAclAdminState.description: This object indicates the global IP ACL state.

cienaCesAclCacheHit.name: cienaCesAclCacheHit
cienaCesAclCacheHit.description: This object indicates the number of lookups satisfied by a cache hit.

cienaCesAclNoHit.name: cienaCesAclNoHit
cienaCesAclNoHit.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because the source ip address did not match a table entry.

cienaCesAclBadPort.name: cienaCesAclBadPort
cienaCesAclBadPort.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because the ingress port was disallowed by a table entry.

cienaCesAclBadDscp.name: cienaCesAclBadDscp
cienaCesAclBadDscp.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because the ingress DSCP value was disallowed by a table entry.

cienaCesAclOperState.name: cienaCesAclOperState
cienaCesAclOperState.description: This object indicates the current operational state of the IP ACL system.

cienaCesAclInUseEntries.name: cienaCesAclInUseEntries
cienaCesAclInUseEntries.description: This object indicates the number of IP ACL rules that are currently configured.

cienaCesAclMaxEntries.name: cienaCesAclMaxEntries
cienaCesAclMaxEntries.description: This object indicates the maximum number of IP ACL rules that can be configured.

cienaCesAclBadProtocol.name: cienaCesAclBadProtocol
cienaCesAclBadProtocol.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because protocol didn't match protocol allowed for matching src/dst subnet

cienaCesAclTable.name: cienaCesAclTable
cienaCesAclTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the parameters for the IP ACL table.

cienaCesAclEntry.name: cienaCesAclEntry
cienaCesAclEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cienaCesAclTable.

cienaCesAclEntryInetAddrType.name: cienaCesAclEntryInetAddrType
cienaCesAclEntryInetAddrType.description: This object indicates the IP network type which will be authorized. This OID specifies the Inet address type of the OIDs cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr and cienaCesAclEntryInetPrefixLength. When representing: ipv4 : cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv4 from RFC 4001 ipv6 : cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv6 from RFC 4001

cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr.name: cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr
cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr.description: This object indicates the source IP network address that will be authorized. This OID should be used in conjunction with cienaCesAclEntryInetAddrType and should be compliant with RFC 4001 InetAddressType.

cienaCesAclEntryInetPrefixLength.name: cienaCesAclEntryInetPrefixLength
cienaCesAclEntryInetPrefixLength.description: This object indicates the prefix length for the source IP network that will be authorized. This OID should be used in conjunction with cienaCesAclEntryInetAddrType.

cienaCesAclEntryHits.name: cienaCesAclEntryHits
cienaCesAclEntryHits.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that matched the table entry.

cienaCesAclEntryBadPort.name: cienaCesAclEntryBadPort
cienaCesAclEntryBadPort.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because the ingress port was disallowed by the table entry.

cienaCesAclEntryDscpMask.name: cienaCesAclEntryDscpMask
cienaCesAclEntryDscpMask.description: This object indicates the DSCP values for which IP packets are allowed to ingress. The mask is big endian and each bit, numbered from 0 to 63, represents a DSCP value numbered from 0 to 63. A value of 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF may be used to specify all.

cienaCesAclEntryBadDscp.name: cienaCesAclEntryBadDscp
cienaCesAclEntryBadDscp.description: This object indicates the number of lookups that failed because the ingress DSCP value was disallowed by the table entry.

cienaCesAclEntryPortBitMask.name: cienaCesAclEntryPortBitMask
cienaCesAclEntryPortBitMask.description: This object indicates the physical ports on which frames will be allowed to ingress from. The mask is big endian and each bit, numbered from 0 to 63, represents a physical port numbered from 1 to 64. A value of 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF may be used to specify all ports.

cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddrType.name: cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddrType
cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddrType.description: This object indicates the IP network type which will be authorized. This OID specifies the Inet address type of the OIDs cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddr and cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetPrefixLength. When representing: ipv4 : cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv4 from RFC 4001 ipv6 : cienaCesAclEntryInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv6 from RFC 4001

cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddr.description: This object indicates the IP network address that will be authorized. This OID should be used in conjunction with cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddrType and should be compliant with RFC 4001 InetAddressType.

cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetPrefixLength.name: cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetPrefixLength
cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetPrefixLength.description: This object indicates the prefix length for the IP network that will be authorized. This OID should be used in conjunction with cienaCesAclEntryNotifInetAddrType.

cienaCesExtAclTable.name: cienaCesExtAclTable
cienaCesExtAclTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the parameters for the extended IP ACL table.

cienaCesExtAclEntry.name: cienaCesExtAclEntry
